During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest discussed a range of topics including the controversy surrounding Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg's comments about Donald Trump, the possibility of the US and Russia coordinating military operations in Syria, President Obama's phone call with UK Prime Minister Theresa May, and the President's recent meeting with civil rights leaders and law enforcement officials to discuss race relations and policing. Earnest also addressed questions about the President's plans after leaving office and the Republican Party's platform.